detailedDescription.articleBody:
NAD Electronics is a brand name of an electronics firm whose products include home hi-fi amplifiers and related components. NAD is an abbreviation for New Acoustic Dimension.
The company was founded in London, England, in 1972 by Dr. Martin L. Borish, an electrical engineer with a PhD in physics.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: NAD Electronics एक इलेक्ट्रॉनिक्स फर्म का एक ब्रांड नाम है, जिसके उत्पादों में होम हाई-फाई एम्पलीफायर और संबंधित घटक शामिल हैं, NAD न्यू एकॉस्टिक डायमेंशन का संक्षिप्त नाम है,\n

detailedDescription.articleBody: NAD(P)H dehydrogenase [quinone] 1 is an enzyme that in humans is encoded by the NQO1 gene. This protein-coding gene is a member of the NAD(P)H dehydrogenase family and encodes a 2-electron reductase.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: एनएडी (पी) एच डिहाइड्रोजनेज [क्विनोन] 1 एक एंजाइम है जो मनुष्यों में एनक्यूओ 1 जीन द्वारा एन्कोड किया गया है, यह प्रोटीन-कोडिंग जीन एनएडी (पी) एच डिहाइड्रोजनेज परिवार का सदस्य है और 2-इलेक्ट्रॉन रिडक्टेस को एन्कोड करता है,

detailedDescription.articleBody: A calendar date is a reference to a particular day represented within a calendar system. The calendar date allows the specific day to be identified. The number of days between two dates may be calculated. For example, "24 November 2020" is ten days after "14 November 2020" in the Gregorian calendar. The date of a particular event depends on the observed time zone. For example, the air attack on Pearl Harbor that began at 7:48 a.m. Hawaiian time on 7 December 1941 took place at 3:18 a.m. Japan Standard Time, 8 December in Japan.

detailedDescription.articleBody:
Trousers or pants are an item of clothing that might have originated in Central Asia, worn from the waist to the ankles, covering both legs separately.
Outside North America, the word pants generally means underwear and not trousers.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide is a cofactor central to metabolism. Found in all living cells, NAD is called a dinucleotide because it consists of two nucleotides joined through their phosphate groups.
